peqKRQjn0p8dsuEZYmKV71Db-RA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:3313;s:6:"height";i:5244;s:6:"source";s:101:"https://www.reuters.com/business/bank-america-leaves-wall-street-wondering-about-next-ceo-2021-06-10/";s:6:"domain";s:15:"www.reuters.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:55:{i:0;s:56:"So the question is CEO vs Chairmen who is more powerful.";i:1;s:79:"A Chief Executive Officer or CEO is the highest-ranking officer in the company.";i:2;s:110:"In corporate governance and structure a President of a company holds the title of Chief Operating Officer COO.";i:3;s:129:"In the corporate hierarchy CEO is the 1 highest position in a company and President is considered to be the second one in charge.";i:4;s:14:"Answer 1 of 3.";i:5;s:215:"Ultimately the major or more correctly the majority shareholder as he or they have the power to completely replace the sitting board of directors if they really wanted to and this includes the chairman of the board.";i:6;s:62:"The CEO has power to hire and fire and run the corporation on.";i:7;s:132:"In simple term Yes Chairman do have more powers than a CEO as having the direct indirect powers of hiring and firing the CEO itself.";i:8;s:66:"Although more or less it depends on the Company structure as well.";i:9;s:29:"And guess who has more power.";i:10;s:86:"The board of directors has more power than the CEO because the board can fire the CEO.";i:11;s:91:"However there is one more group that has more power than the CEO or the board of directors.";i:12;s:116:"Thats right The investors have the most power more than the CEO and more than the board of directors in any company.";i:13;s:42:"The chairman holds superiority to the CEO.";i:14;s:151:"As well as having the right to overrule the CEO on major issues the chairman along with the rest of the board makes the decision to hire or fire a CEO.";i:15;s:89:"The exact balance of power between a CEO and a chairman can vary from company to company.";i:16;s:91:"For example in some companies departmental heads are automatically members of the board of.";i:17;s:134:"In simple terms the CEO is the top senior executive over management while the board chairperson is the head of the board of directors.";i:18;s:113:"The CEO is the top decision-maker for the company and the person who oversees the daily operations and logistics.";i:19;s:58:"All of the senior management executives report to the CEO.";i:20;s:52:"Technically the Chairman is the superior of the CEO.";i:21;s:49:"The chairman is the ultimate boss of the company.";i:22;s:113:"The CEO leads the company in terms of executing the agenda approved by the board which is headed by the chairman.";i:23;s:74:"Chief Executive Officer CEO Masters degree Years of management experience.";i:24;s:31:"6 all top executives President.";i:25;s:24:"Masters degree Years of.";i:26;s:123:"On the other hand a CEO is a person who is chosen by the Management to lead the executive operations ie to run the Company.";i:27;s:66:"The CEO is the link between the Board of Director and the Company.";i:28;s:105:"A CEO can be a Director MD Chairman or an employee but no person other than the Director can become a MD.";i:29;s:52:"For details of MD you can look up the Companies Act.";i:30;s:138:"In general the chief executive officer CEO is considered the highest-ranking officer in a company while the president is second in charge.";i:31;s:46:"However in corporate governance and structure.";i:32;s:82:"CEO has powers to manage the business but shall be in day to day control of Board.";i:33;s:199:"A careful reading of legal definitions of these three designations under the Indian Companies Act 2013 show Managing Director may have fewer powers than Manager but more than Chief Executive Officer.";i:34;s:334:"Whereas Chairman is often the head of the board of directors President is the actual head of the company with additional titles of CO or CEO President looks after day to day affairs of the company whereas chairman is more concerned with profitability of the company as he is answerable to the shareholders who elect the board members.";i:35;s:92:"The balance of power between the CEO and the chairman varies widely from company to company.";i:36;s:74:"Because the CEO cannot make major moves without the boards assent and his.";i:37;s:108:"As the head of the board of directors this gives the chairman a higher rank within the company than the CEO.";i:38;s:44:"This isnt the case at all companies however.";i:39;s:123:"In a number of companies the CEO actually serves as the chairman of the board in addition to acting as the chief executive.";i:40;s:162:"An additional year of CEO tenure is associated with a 22 increase in the probability that the CEO is also board chairman and a 24 increase in annual compensation.";i:41;s:91:"A second broad dynamic bargaining prediction is that more powerful CEOs are less likely to.";i:42;s:108:"The Chairman of the Board The Chairman of the Board shall be the chief executive officer of the Corporation.";i:43;s:282:"He shall direct coordinate and control the Corporations business and activities and its operating expenses and capital expenditures and shall have general authority to exercise all the powers necessary for the chief executive officer of the Corporation all in accordance with basic.";i:44;s:283:"A nonexecutive chair with little or no industry competency was observed to be more likely to be circumvented or pleasantly tolerated but managed by the CEO in one instance the CEO was said to own the chair rather than a good reliable liaison and mentor between the board and the CEO.";i:45;s:105:"The relationship between the chair and CEO is important and likely to be productive when there is mutual.";i:46;s:188:"CEOs usually have the power to make binding decisions for the company without prior approval from the board of directors and CEOs may fire or hire for any position directly in the company.";i:47;s:153:"Presidents on the other hand generally act more as top-tier managers with power over personnel but lack the power to single-handedly alter the course of.";i:48;s:47:"Boards and CEOs both make high-level decisions.";i:49;s:91:"The exact difference between their roles is not set in stone but decided by company policy.";i:50;s:81:"At some corporations for example the CEO sits on the board even serving as chair.";i:51;s:111:"Board responsibilities include choosing and firing the CEO approving major policies and making major decisions.";i:52;s:65:"Legally you have no more power as chairman than another director.";i:53;s:197:"You might have added responsibilities such as running board meetings but the chairman has very little formal power except in organisations where there is a special charter about the chairmans role.";i:54;s:60:"The chairman usually has to rely on exerting informal power.";}}